  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Shan - Conflict-sensitive humanitarian response to IDPs and conflict-affected communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The needs of communities affected by conflict in protracted crises are met in a way that restores livelihoods, maintains dignity, and builds resilience&#x2019;. To identify and tackle the root causes of conflict and violence, including gender-based violence.To empower target communities to anticipate and adapt to crises and risks related to conflict, violence</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project area in Northern Shan will include 5 IDP camps (201 HHs with a population of 931 IDPs) and 15 villages (1143  HHs with a population of 5865 people) in Namtu and Manton townships.The focus in Northern Shan will strongly be on Livelihoods, GBV and protection especially human trafficking and developing local capacity. Livelihood assistance,cash assistance and technical mentoring support and knowledge and skill building of target beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
